 shopping malls, and factories, and received national recognition for his contributions. This richly illustrated book includes an interview with John C. Parkin and essays that examine the incorporation of art in built architecture, the influence of architectural photography in defining Modern architecture to a Canadian public, the importance of architectural archives, and the corporate structure of a large, highly successful Canadian architectural firm.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArchitectural photography -- Canada -- History -- 20th century. 0aArchitectural photographyzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aArchitecture -- Canada -- Archival resources -- History -- 20th century. 0aArchitecture -- Canada -- History -- 20th century. 0aArchitecturezCanadaxArchival resourcesxHistoryy20th century. 0aArchitecturezCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aArchitecture, Modern -- 20th century. 0aArchitecture, Moderny20th century. 0aArt and architecture -- Canada -- History -- 20th century. 0aArt and architecturezCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aParkin, John Cresswell, -- 1922-1988 -- Criticism and interpretation. 0aParkin, John Cresswell, -- 1922-1988 -- Interviews.1 aFraser, Linda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcMordie, Michael J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcMordie, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSimmins, Geoffrey, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSimmins, Geoffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSribney, Julie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013z978311127412608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertA